iling eyes. Luzhin thought vaguely that he resembled the peasant from the mill, but the resemblance immediately vanished when the man spoke: 'Karasho?' he inquired amiably. 'Who are you?' asked Luzhin in German. 'A friend,'

replied the gentleman, 'a faithful friend. You have been sick but now you are well. Do you hear? You are quite well.' Luzhin began to meditate on these words, but the man did not allow him to finish and said sympathetically: 'You must lie quiet. Rest. Get lots of sleep.'

